#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.97"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.97:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.97:0.2"
msgid "10. Asuravagga "
msgstr "10. Demons "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.97:0.3"
msgid "97. Khippanisantisutta "
msgstr "97. Quick-witted "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.97:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.97:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><ol>
msgctxt "an4.97:1.3"
msgid "Attahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, parahitāya paṭipanno no attahitāya, nevattahitāya paṭipanno no parahitāya, attahitāya ceva paṭipanno parahitāya ca. "
msgstr "~One who practices to benefit themselves, but not others; ~one who practices to benefit others, but not themselves; ~one who practices to benefit neither themselves nor others; and ~one who practices to benefit both themselves and others. "

#. HTML: </ol><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.97:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya? "
msgstr "And how does a person practice to benefit themselves, but not others? "

#. VAR: dhārakajātiko → dhāraṇajātiko (mr)
#. VAR: dhātānañca → dhatānañca (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.97:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo khippanisantī ca hoti kusalesu dhammesu, sutānañca dhammānaṃ dhārakajātiko hoti, dhātānañca dhammānaṃ atthūpaparikkhī hoti atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya, dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti; "
msgstr "It’s when a person is quick-witted when it comes to skillful teachings. They readily memorize the teachings they’ve heard. They examine the meaning of teachings they’ve memorized. Understanding the meaning and the teaching, they practice accordingly. "

#. VAR: samādapako → samādāpako (?)
msgctxt "an4.97:2.3"
msgid "no ca kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā, no ca sandassako hoti samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnaṃ. "
msgstr "But they’re not a good speaker. Their voice isn’t polished, clear, articulate, and doesn’t express the meaning. They don’t educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire their spiritual companions. "

msgctxt "an4.97:2.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya. "
msgstr "That’s how a person practices to benefit themselves, but not others. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.97:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo parahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no attahitāya? "
msgstr "And how does a person practice to benefit others, but not themselves? "

msgctxt "an4.97:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na heva kho khippanisantī hoti kusalesu dhammesu, no ca sutānaṃ dhammānaṃ dhārakajātiko hoti, no ca dhātānaṃ dhammānaṃ atthūpaparikkhī hoti, no ca atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti; "
msgstr "It’s when a person is not quick-witted when it comes to skillful teachings. … "

msgctxt "an4.97:3.3"
msgid "kalyāṇavāco ca hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā, sandassako ca hoti samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnaṃ. "
msgstr "But they’re a good speaker. … "

msgctxt "an4.97:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo parahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no attahitāya. "
msgstr "That’s how a person practices to benefit others, but not themselves. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.98, sc4
msgctxt "an4.97:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya? "
msgstr "And how does a person practice to benefit neither themselves nor others? "

msgctxt "an4.97:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na heva kho khippanisantī hoti kusalesu dhammesu, no ca sutānaṃ dhammānaṃ dhārakajātiko hoti, no ca dhātānaṃ dhammānaṃ atthūpaparikkhī hoti, no ca atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti; "
msgstr "It’s when a person is not quick-witted when it comes to skillful teachings. … "

msgctxt "an4.97:4.3"
msgid "no ca kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā, no ca sandassako hoti samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnaṃ. "
msgstr "Nor are they a good speaker. … "

msgctxt "an4.97:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattahitāya paṭipanno hoti, no parahitāya. "
msgstr "That’s how a person practices to benefit neither themselves nor others. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.97:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya ceva paṭipanno hoti parahitāya ca? "
msgstr "And how does a person practice to benefit both themselves and others? "

msgctxt "an4.97:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo khippanisantī ca hoti kusalesu dhammesu, sutānañca dhammānaṃ dhārakajātiko hoti, dhātānañca dhammānaṃ atthūpaparikkhī hoti atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya, dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti; "
msgstr "It’s when a person is quick-witted when it comes to skillful teachings. … "

msgctxt "an4.97:5.3"
msgid "kalyāṇavāco ca hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā, sandassako ca hoti samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnaṃ. "
msgstr "And they’re a good speaker. … "

msgctxt "an4.97:5.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo attahitāya ceva paṭipanno hoti parahitāya ca. "
msgstr "That’s how a person practices to benefit both themselves and others. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.97:5.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four people found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.97:5.6"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

